    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' colspan='2'>THE GREAT DIVIDE</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
		<td align='left' class='db' vAlign='top'><img align=right src='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/images/greatdivide.jpg'><p>Besides containing a spectacular waterfall which marks the entrance to the
Coldain City of <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/zones.asp?Action=Description&Id=115">Thurgadin</a>
the Great Divide has many exciting opportunities to offer.</p>
<p>This zone contains the Shardwurm Cave, a little downstream from the
Thurgadin Falls in a deep cave.  These drop mid level velious spells for
caster classes, and some basic items.  The Wurms are also factionless, and
a great spot to have some relatively safe fun with a group of 40+ players.</p>
<p>You can also take this zone up into <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/zones.asp?Action=Description&Id=124">Velketor's
Labyrinth</a>.   This is a relatively high level dungeon.</p>
<p>The Great Divide zone does have a portal to it, but you will need to pick up
the key within it's circle.  The key spawns on the ground every minute and
is soul bound.</p>
<p>If you wish to be more adventurous there is a Frost Giant fort in the zone,
but beware of faction hits.  </p>
<p>The only way into the Great Divide besides a portal is from the <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/zones.asp?Action=Description&Id=109">Eastern
Wastes</a>.  The zone has a number of good areas for getting comfortable in
Velious, with some good safe resting spots near the Thurga Falls provided your
faction with the Coldain Dwarfs is sufficient.</p></td>
		<td width='18%' align='right' class='db' valign='top'><font class=dbti>Zone Information</font><br><a href='http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/forumdisplay.cgi?action=topics&forum=The+Great+Divide&number=259&DaysPrune=5&LastLogin='>Forum</a><br><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/zones.asp?Action=ListByMonsters&SubAction=ShowAll&ZoneId=113'>Monsters</a><br><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/zones.asp?Action=ListItems&SubAction=ShowAll&ZoneId=113'>Items</a><br> <a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/data/maps.asp?Action=Description&Id=113'>Map</a>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td colspan=2>
  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>ZONE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>PORTING TO THE GREAT DIVIDE</span><b>, By Arvael</b> <small>(2/18/2001)</small><br><br>The tooth is required to port to the Great Divide and every member of the porting group must carry one.   This means that you have to make the run here at least once before it is possible to port to this location with a group.<P>
 
The wurms in the cave drop various mid-level SoV spells, so they are camped usually.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>LEVELING AT 29-MID30S</span><b>, By Blundor</b> <small>(2/7/2001)</small><br><br>If you are a lower level and wish to level here, the best place to go is to the Kodiak cave with a good group.  At 29 I was able to tank these guys pretty well.  Snare/Fear kiting is pretty easy to do with these guys if you pull them out of the cave first.  My first group here was me, a 34 Ranger, and a 35 Chanter.  We were able to kill them easily using fear and snare.  They hit hard, but fearing will keep tham from that.  The second group I was in included me (lowest at 29), Chanter, Druid, Shaman, Mage, and a Ranger.  All of between 29 and 35.  We were able to take on several of these at a time and only stopped every 20 minutes or so to med back to full.  Watch for roamers by the entrance, though.  Watch the Savage Kodiaks, too.  They are tough.  These guys only drop (so far) one item of any interest which are Kodiak Claws.  Usually they drop nothing, so this is no good for loot, but really good for exp.  I was able to make 2 bubs here in about 2 and a half hours.  The zone is closeby, too.  Just run straight above the cave entrance and you will see it.  Easy escape route if you need to evac.  Good luck!<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>EXP AT 44</span><b>, By Rosvineer</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>I have seen no wurms but young shardwurms that were green to me at 44.  And some of the young ones were blue.  In the caves, there are no greenies to me at 44.  They are all blue but the broodmother who is high red.  There are Ancient, Elder, Crystaline and Guardian Shardwurms in these tunnels.  <P>I have not seen a crystaline yet but all others are in fact still giving exp at 44.  Plus there are giants wandering, and at the fort, that are blue to yellow.  Plus at least one named that is red.  <P>All mino's called Tizmak are green and most of the kodiaks as well.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>GREAT DIVIDE OPINION</span><b>, By Tarn</b> <small>(1/28/2001)</small><br><br>
<p>This zone is good exp for levels 35 to 40. Depending on which faction you
wish, you can either hunt Storm Giants or Dwarves here. Melee types can get
bound at either the storm giant city or dwarf city making the run for corpses
rather easy. For lower 30's people the mino caves are great exp. The spawns are
quick and they aren't very strong. The loot isn't very good, though the Tizmak
armor looks cool. There is a Worm tunnel at the opposite end of the water from Thurgadin.
Most were green to me (level 38) and I didn't hunt them. I did see many higher
level people killing them, but doubt that they got exp. They must have decent
drops, but I am only guessing at that.</p>
<p>Storm Giants are rather easy for a small group. A healer and myself (rogue)
were easily taking them on. They drop around 3pp, some velious weapons, and
rarely toes (cleric quest) and Storm Giant beard (storm strength, charges). I
was unable to use it. I am unaware of what level you have to be to use the
charges, but it's higher then 38. You will need to be careful around here as the
giants and the wolves both train. They do not appear to have a large aggro
range, but they will attack anyone who comes close enough regardless of level.
They constantly attack a level 59 cleric who had bad Giant faction.</p>
<p>There is also a druid ring and wizard port located in this zone. The Wizard
port is located in a spot that is constantly patrolled by giants and could be a
problem for those with bad faction. The druid port is off in the middle of
nowhere and doesn't appear to have many MoBs around it. There is a tooth in the
middle of the port that has a respawn of just a few seconds. I have heard that
it is needed to port into this port, but haven't confirmed this as I haven't
seen anyone port to it.</p>
<p>All in all I like this zone a lot. The spawns are fast and there are a lot of
them. The zone generally has a lot of people in it so buffs were easy to get.
Higher levels travel through here a lot using the cities or working on faction.
This will probably be a busy zone, but one well worth being busy.</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
